 {'content': "It sounds like an entertaining movie. I'll probably watch it tonight.", 'role': 'user'}
 {'content': 'Great!  In the film, Johnson plays a military man who returns to his hometown to be the sheriff.  Main characters include Ivan, played by Brian Anthony Wilson, who controls a gang that’s been active in the town; Bill, a soldier who was paralyzed in combat and needs to find a new purpose in life; Linda, the grieving widow of a former sheriff who was murdered by Ivan’s gang; and his mischievous aunt, Allie.  It was initially released in 2009, but rarely shown as the film was a box office failure.  However, it did achieve a good overall rating on review aggregator Rotten Tomatoes.  Many critics praised the film for having a neat setup, though some found the plot a bit too predictable.  In 2017, the film was released in theaters in the UK and Australia.', 'role': 'assistant'}]

