[{'content': 'How do you make homemade fabric softener?', 'role': 'user'}
 {'content': 'To make homemade fabric softener, you can mix a few tablespoons of baking soda into a small basin of warm water, and then soak your clothes in the mixture.  Baking soda is a mild detergent that will soften your clothes, and the warm water will enhance the softening effects.  You can also add a few drops of essential oils, such as lavender oil, for an even softer smell.  Some people also like to mix in a few tablespoons of vinegar, since vinegar helps to remove soap residue from clothes.', 'role': 'assistant'}
 {'content': "I've seen some people add vinegar, is that a good idea?", 'role': 'user'}
 {'content': 'Yes, adding vinegar to homemade fabric softener is a good idea!  Adding vinegar to softener will help to remove soap residue from clothes, as well as add a refreshing scent.  Additionally, vinegar is a natural softening agent that will make your clothes softer and smoother, making them easier to wash and dry.  Some people also like to add lemon juice to softener, which can impart a refreshing lemon scent to clothing.', 'role': 'assistant'}
 {'content': 'Thanks.', 'role': 'user'}
 {'content': "You're very welcome!  Making homemade fabric softener is easy and inexpensive, and it can help to soften your clothes and improve their smell.  Making softener at home is also environmentally friendly, since it reduces the amount of chemical detergents you use.  Homemade softener is a great way to freshen up your clothes and make them softer.", 'role': 'assistant'}]

