[{'content': 'I want to make italian meatballs. What ingredients do I need?', 'role': 'user'}
 {'content': 'Italian meatballs are usually made with ground beef, eggs, garlic, and some kind of breadcrumbs or breadcrumbs mixed in. You could make meatballs from scratch with meat and eggs, or you could use store-bought meatballs and add the other ingredients.', 'role': 'assistant'}
 {'content': 'So what kind of meat and breadcrumbs?', 'role': 'user'}
 {'content': 'Ground beef is the most important ingredient, it should be 85% or more ground beef, and 15% or less fat. I recommend organic grass-fed beef, and the meat should be ground very finely, so that it’s not chunky. If you use store-bought meatballs, make sure they’re all ground meat, and not a mixture of meat and vegetables or anything else. 

For the eggs, I recommend organic eggs and to make sure they’re not cooked in any way beforehand.

For the breadcrumbs or breadcrumbs mixed in, you might want to use panko breadcrumbs (or any kind of breadcrumbs ground very finely), and you might also want to mix some shredded Italian-style bread into the meat mixture to help the meatballs hold together. I recommend making your meat mixture in a food processor, mixing in the eggs, and then combining the meat mixture with the breadcrumbs (or adding the breadcrumbs to the meat mixture), and forming the meatballs by hand. 

You can also make meatballs and then bake them in the oven. To make the meat mixture, start with the ground meat and eggs, then add the breadcrumbs and/or breadcrumbs and shredded bread and mix everything', 'role': 'assistant'}]

