Creationists, who maintain a belief in a theistic deity, often interpret scientific descriptions of the origins of the universe as incompatible with their ideas of the divine creator.  However, this position runs in contrast with a number of stories and traditions reaching back into antiquity and spanning many diverse religious cultures, including Judaism, Christianity, and Islam.  Although these traditions vary in many respects, they generally accept some concept of a higher creative force responsible for the origin and evolution of our universe -- a "beginning" without invoking faith or mystery.  

