The science of cosmology is constantly advancing and attempting to further understand the big bang.  In particular, scientific efforts to understand the “initial state” of the early universe -- what the content, conditions, and circumstances were from the big bang until shortly after the first particles formed -- continue to progress using observational and experimental models.  According to current scientific understanding, fundamental forces and physical laws were governed by highly symmetric and well-ordered conditions during the period of our universe that immediately followed the big bang.  These conditions needed to be in place for particles, energy, and physical forces and fields', 'role': 'assistant'}
