[{'content': 'What does the saying "the tables have turned" mean?', 'role': 'user'}
 {'content': 'This is an idiomatic expression referring to the reversal of some power or dominance relationship.  Generally, it means circumstances have changed such that the current power dynamic between two opponents or conflict parties has been flipped, with the usual power balance or relationship between them now reversed.', 'role': 'assistant'}
