 {'content': 'This passage is describing the origins and history of the Salsa dance and musical style, which has roots in Cuba and Puerto Rico and spread rapidly worldwide in the 1960s, and which is now an extremely popular genre of Latin music with many different regional varieties and fused with many different kinds of global musical styles. It is performed at dance parties in nightclubs, bars, restaurants, hotels, wedding receptions, fairs and festivals throughout the world and is also enjoyed by people of all ages away from the dance floor through listening. It is easily distinguished from other Latin styles by its characteristic rhythm of 3 steps for every 4 beats of music.', 'role': 'assistant'}
